Get Maven 3.0.4 binary distribution using the following command:
	wget ftp://mirror.reverse.net/pub/apache/maven/maven-3/3.2.5/binaries/apache-maven-3.2.5-bin.tar.gz

Unpack the binary distribution using the following command:
	tar -zxf apache-maven-3.2.5-bin.tar.gz

Move uncompressed "apache-maven-3.2.5" directory to the /usr/local directory using this command:
	sudo mv apache-maven-3.2.5 /usr/local

Edit bashrc file.
	sudo nano ~/.bashrc
	
paste lines in bashrc file.
	export M2_HOME=/usr/local/apache-maven-3.2.5
	export M2=$M2_HOME/bin
	export MAVEN_OPTS="-Xms1024m -Xmx4096m"
	export PATH=$M2:$PATH

save & exit
	save--> ctrl+o  after enter
	exit--> ctrl+x

refresh bashrc file
 . ~/.bashrc
 
Verify for correct installation using the following comman:
	mvn --version

It should print the following information:
	Apache Maven 3.2.5 (12a6b3acb947671f09b81f49094c53f426d8cea1; 2014-12-14T22:59:23+05:30)
	Maven home: /usr/local/apache-maven-3.2.5
	Java version: 1.7.0_75, vendor: Oracle Corporation
	Java home: /usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.7.0_75/jre
	Default locale: en_US, platform encoding: UTF-8
	OS name: "linux", version: "3.16.0-30-generic", arch: "amd64", family: "unix"
